---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy — Notchi" description="Notchi privacy policy. Your data stays on your Mac.">
  <Nav />
  <article class="legal">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: March 2025</p>

    <h2>Your data stays on your Mac</h2>
    <p>Notchi runs entirely on your Mac. It receives Claude Code and Codex events through a local Unix socket and processes everything locally. No code, file paths, or session content ever leaves your device.</p>

    <h2>API usage tracking</h2>
    <p>If you connect your Anthropic API key to view usage stats, the app makes requests directly to the Anthropic API to fetch your usage data. No data is sent to Notchi servers.</p>

    <h2>Update checks</h2>
    <p>Notchi uses the Sparkle framework to check for updates. This sends your app version and macOS version to check for new releases. No personal information is included.</p>

    <h2>No account required</h2>
    <p>Notchi does not require registration, login, or any personal information to use.</p>

    <h2>This website</h2>
    <p>This is a static site hosted on Cloudflare Pages. No cookies, no tracking, no analytics.</p>
  </article>
  <Footer />
</Base>
